# 📄 Product Requirements Document (PRD)

## 🧭 Product Name

**GeoJobs – Map-based Job Discovery Platform (MVP)**

---

## 🎯 Objective

Allow users to discover jobs visually on a **map**, using a **lightweight MVP setup (CSV-based data)** with ability to scale to DB later.

---

## 👤 Target Users

* Job seekers (freshers + experienced)
* Users targeting specific areas (e.g., Whitefield, ORR)
* Domain-focused candidates

---

## 🚀 Core Features

### 1. Location-Based Job Discovery

* User selects:

  * Location (dropdown will only contain Bangalore as of now)
  * Job role/category (should be pre-defined derived from datasource)
* Map displays **company pins**

---

### 2. Company Map Pins

* Each company shown as:

  * 📍 Marker with **logo (18×18 static/random icon)**
* Cluster markers when zoomed out

---

### 3. Job Listings per Company

* On clicking a pin:

  * Show list:

    * Job Title
    * Posted Date
    * Apply Link
* Redirect externally

---

### 4. Role-Based Filtering

* Predefined job categories (50 roles)
* Multi-select filter
* Search input

---

### 5. Logo Handling (MVP)

* No external API
* Use:

  * Static logo set OR
  * Random icon per company
* Mapping:

  * `company_name → logo_file`

---

## 🗂 Data Source (MVP)

### Primary Source: CSV

Structure:

```csv
Company Name,Location,Job Title,Posted On,Apply Link
```

Additional derived fields:

* latitude (pre-mapped)
* longitude (pre-mapped)
* role_category (tagged)

---

## 🔄 Data Layer Strategy

### Config-Based Source Switching

```json
{
  "DATA_SOURCE": "csv" // or "postgres"
}
```

---

### CSV Mode (MVP)

* Load CSV into memory (or cache)
* Parse → group by company
* Fast, no infra required

---

### Postgres Mode (Future)

* Replace CSV loader with DB queries
* Same response format (adapter pattern)

---

## 🧱 Data Model (Unified Interface)

### Company

* id
* name
* latitude
* longitude
* logo

### Job

* id
* company_id
* title
* role_category
* posted_on
* apply_link

---

## 🖥️ Tech Stack (MVP)

### Frontend

* React
* Leaflet / Google Maps
* Tailwind

### Backend

* Node.js / FastAPI
* CSV parser

---

## ⚡ MVP Scope (2 Weeks)

* Load jobs from CSV
* Map with company pins
* Click → job list popup
* Role filtering
* Static/random logos
* Config switch (CSV → DB ready)

---

## 📈 Success Metrics

* Job clicks
* Map interactions
* Session duration

---

## ⚠️ Constraints

* CSV is static (no real-time updates)
* Manual geo-tagging required
* Logo accuracy limited (random/static)

---

## 🔮 Future Enhancements

* Switch to Postgres
* Automated job ingestion pipeline
* Real company logos (optional later)
* AI-based recommendations

---

## ✅ Summary

A **lean MVP** using **CSV + static logos + map UI**, designed with a **clean abstraction layer** to seamlessly migrate to Postgres and live data pipelines later.
